title: Prostynia, Choszczno County
text:
Prostynia is a <a href="village">village</a> in the administrative district of <a href="Gmina%20Drawno">Gmina Drawno</a>, within <a href="Choszczno%20County">Choszczno County</a>, <a href="West%20Pomeranian%20Voivodeship">West Pomeranian Voivodeship</a>, in north-western <a href="Poland">Poland</a>. It lies approximately north of <a href="Drawno">Drawno</a>, north-east of <a href="Choszczno">Choszczno</a>, and east of the regional capital <a href="Szczecin">Szczecin</a>.
Before 1945 the area was part of <a href="Germany">Germany</a>.
